description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Matron Women’s services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Northampton General Hospital we provide general acute services and hyper-acute stroke, vascular and renal services to people living in Northamptonshire. As well as this we are an accredited cancer center and provide cancer services to a wider population of Northamptonshire and parts of Buckinghamshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are proud to be the first hospital in the UK to have obtained Pathway to Excellence® designated accreditation from the American nurses credentialing center (ANCC).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We celebrate staff achievements and value the importance of working as one big team. That’s why we talk about Team NGH. It’s all about working together to provide the best possible care for our patients and supporting each other to grow and develop our skills. We are driven to helping you to be the best you can be.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply today and join the largest family in Northamptonshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Matron Women services (band 8a) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time to be joining Northampton General Hospital, not only have we just formed a group hospital model with Kettering General but we are the only acute hospital in the country to be accredited with ‘Pathway to Excellence®’, which makes us feel very proud. Proud that we achieved recognition as an organisation, but prouder by the fact we could not have achieved it, if our staff did not agree that NGH is a great place to work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Staff recognition is important to us, we fully support the international DAISY awards and we partner with the Cavell Trust. These are all things that you will see that sets Northampton General Hospital apart from everyone else&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity for a highly motivated, inspirational nurse leader who is committed to providing first class care to women has arisen. Our women’s services provide a wealth of specialist services including; Emergency, Outpatient and Inpatient care. We have a large team of specialist nurses who manage their own caseloads and run their own colposcopy, hysteroscopy and urogynaecology clinics. Our Emergency pregnancy assessment unit is run by nurses who work independently, we have 5 nurse sonographers who support our women through fertility, pregnancy and miscarriage. We have recently developed our elective surgical pathway to facilitate women’s Gynaecology and breast surgery in a safe area. The nursing and Clincial teams are motivated to providing first class care and there are lots of opportunities for professional development within the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for developing and managing women’s services and managing the Trusts discharge suite. This is a high profile role working closely with the Clinical Director and Directorate manager to provide leadership and management to the nursing teams. You will ensure that care delivery is safe, effective, well led and responsive. If you are a highly visible, engaging professional lead that can influence and continue to develop our women’s services then please get in touch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Joanne Smith, Job title: Interim Associate Director Nursing Women&#39;s Children&#39;s , Oncology, Haematology and Cancer services, Email addres: sjoanne.smith2@ngh.nhs.uk Telephone number: 07590617206&lt;/p&gt;
